  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, a long prison sentence is disproportionate given the amount stolen and the lack of a criminal history. The outburst by the spectator is disregarded as it is prejudicial and irrelevant to the sentencing guidelines. A term of 6 months serves as a punitive measure that reflects the gravity of the offense while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
